Roster
======

Roster is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

This project is a fork of and built on top of:

  claude-code-go
    Repository: https://github.com/tunsuy/claude-code-go
    License:    MIT (see LICENSE.upstream for the original license text)
    Copyright:  (c) 2024 Anthropic, PBC

Roster retains the upstream license file as `LICENSE.upstream` to satisfy
the MIT attribution requirement, and applies the same MIT terms to all
Roster-specific additions and modifications.

Roster also draws design inspiration (but no code) from Anthropic's
Claude Code TypeScript implementation, which is proprietary software
belonging to Anthropic, PBC. Any conceptual borrowings (e.g. KAIROS-like
proactive loops, autoDream-style maintenance subagents, Undercover Mode,
Skills abstraction, Remote API trigger pattern) are reimplemented from
scratch in Go without copying source from that codebase.
